A law firm, Templars, has joined forces with an anti-gender-based violence organisation, the Women at Risk International Foundation (WARIF) in the battle to end violence against women and girls. The firm has implemented a series of training sessions geared towards awareness creation and the prevention of gender-based violence. It has also provided expert witness training to the WARIF medical team. These sessions enlighten the medical personnel at the organisation on the rules guiding legal proceedings, relevant criminal law and the importance of evidence when prosecuting the offence of rape or sexual assault. WARIF Founder, Dr Kemi DaSilva-Ibru, said: “We are proud of our long-standing partnership with Templars, a law firm with a stellar reputation providing legal support to the organisation and the amplification of our initiatives such as the No Tolerance Campaign.   Investors’ suit to recover N11.79b resumes Feb 12     Prayers held for Bello’s presidential ambition,…     Refuse dumps overrun Anambra cities   - Advertisement - “We appreciate the support given to us by Templars in the elimination of gender-based violence in Nigeria.” Managing Partner at Templars, Mr. Oghogho Akpata, said: “We are committed to fighting against all forms of violence against women and children. “Our Partnership with WARIF has been longstanding and instrumental in creating awareness on gender-based violence and providing legal services to assist the organisation in achieving its set goals. “We are glad to see the efforts the team at WARIF has made to date.” WARIF addresses the prevalence of rape, sexual violence, and human trafficking in communities across Nigeria.